history.content:
CS161 contains security and networking information that everyone in the field should know. Of course, 162 and 170 are seen as rite of passage courses.

I've enjoyed most of 186 and 188, though I'm told 188 isn't that useful. And beware what you've been told about 188; the difficulty in that class seems to have ramped up from previous semesters. After reviewing past homeworks and projects prior to taking 186 this semester, it seems the same can be said about that class as well.

I don't know about waitlists for those classes in the spring. It looks like you'll have a good shot at 186, but I would add another class like 161 as a backup if you're set on two technicals.

I'm wondering if people had advice for classes they would recommend taking in Spring 2021 for the first CS upper div's, having just taken 61C and 70 this semester for someone planning to double major in Econ and CS. Right now, I'm taking Econ141, Econ 136, and am on the waitlist #76 for CS186 and #397 on the waitlist for CS188.

In regard to this schedule, would it be a reasonable workload? If I were to choose one of CS186 or CS188, what would be the merits to taking each as the first CS upper div? Are there other CS classes that I should also consider taking (Data 100, CS170, or otherwise)? And what are the chances of getting off the waitlist for each class?

Any advice would be much appreciated-thank you and Happy Thanksgiving!
history.subject: Recommendations for Spring 2021 classes?
